		<td class="alt2" style="border:1px inset">
			
				<div>
					Originally Posted by <strong>Pyron</strong>
					<a href="showthread.php?p=1379696#post1379696" rel="nofollow"><img class="inlineimg" src="images/buttons/viewpost.gif" border="0" alt="View Post" /></a>
				</div>
				<div style="font-style:italic">Honestly, I think the vigilante solution is the best solution in this case.  There's an old saw that hard cases make poor law, and I agree with that.  However, that also implies that sometimes the law is not the best way to deal with an exceptional situation .<br />
<br />
The fact that ANY evidence can be excluded is something that is broken in both the U.S. and the Canadian system.  The easiest way to fix that is to remove all exclusions and allow all available evidence to be heard.  That removes the whole problem with classifying her as a Dangerous Offender.<br />
<br />
