<br />
Courage doesnt guarantee success.  Perhaps, if someone had stepped in, they could have saved him.  Or perhaps they would have stopped the guy but the kid would have bled to death.  Or perhaps they would have been too late entirely.  Perhaps they would even have died in the process.<br />
<br />
There are lots of uncertainties when contemplating the results of any action.  But two things that are NOT undertain:<br />
1) If they had stepped in to save him, they would not have been cowards, but Decent Human Beings.<br />
2) The way things played out, they are craven, spineless, and have utterly forgotten the faces of their fathers.</div>
